This paper deals with the problem of maximizing directed information, which is a concept from information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves optimization algorithms and numerical examples, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of memory and complexity, which could be relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability).
